text:
hi, my name is roxanne darling (@roxannedarling) and this is my week to takeover instagram from the los angeles center of photography (lacp) @la_centerofphoto. i am an emerging artist currently living in santa fe, nm. i love that lacp welcomes out-of-state photographers to be part of their community. this week, let's talk about bodies, nature, and getting older!

image: 
i am: saying goodbye to my merchandized self

the photos i’m sharing this week are of me, from my series of portraits in nature. as a 66-year-old woman and emerging artist, i’m exploring the:
* the natural desire to be unclothed outdoors, in the privacy of precious places;
* a newly discovered quality of self-acceptance for my aging self;
* an appetite to create art from the female gaze, as a type of reclaiming my time, my body, and my point of view.

the photos were taken in 2017-2018 on an extended rv trip around the western us with my partner. in many cases, the place itself spoke up first and invited me to explore ways of finding myself in nature. as a card-carrying member of the #metoo movement, i hope this work conveys a type of freedom of self-expression that is possible regardless of one’s painful past experiences.

the photos were shot using several cameras: iphone, dji drone, and a canon dslr. all images have been cropped square; some images have been slightly modified to meet instagram rules. *
*
*
#lacpinstagramtakeover #lacp #losangelescenterofphotography #lacpmember #lacenterofphoto #womenphotographers #picoftheday #iam #santafeartist #freethinker

text: feb 23. "how could you say such a thing? that's so- it's so wrong! i mean, remember the way he all taught astronomy in high school? it was so much fun." "of course it was fun. i wasn't bashing on astronomy. it inspired me to get my phd remember?" "exactly! and he did that. he helped you become who you are today." "he doesn't deserve credit for all that i am. he was an influence in my life, just like everyone else has been. i'm not saying he was a bad teacher. i'm saying he was a bad person. those aren't mutually exclusive." "i just can't believe you would do such a thing. everyone will learn the truth once word gets out. you are going to ruin everything for him. what about his family? his three kids? i've babysat them!" "so what? they can learn the truth from someone else? or so that they can learn he likes to touch kids from their own experience? i'm done protecting him. and even if you don't believe, someone will." "they are just going to call you crazy!" "and what female hasn't been called crazy? enough of us have been silenced. but i won't do it anymore. i deserve to have a voice." #inspiredby #rollinscollege #theatre #johnproctoristhevillain #welldone #pictureis #irrelevant #storytelling #story #metoo #metoomovement #thecrucible #believe #womenempowerment #writemore #writerlife

text:
tomorrow on @hollywoodandbeyondshow with @stevenjbrittingham podcast features two amazing guests discussing their powerful new documentary:

the topic is one that no longer can be denied, ignored or swept under the rug. sexual harassment. jobs for sexual favors. even rape. the casting couch is about to get rocked. 
my special guests andrea evans (one life to live /the bold and the beautiful) and director minh collins have a lot to say about their new documentary film ‘rocking the couch’. we discuss the situation that has plagued hollywood and so many other industries on the next episode.

available sunday, february 24th 
9am et / 6am pt “meaningful interviews”

photos courtesy of: andrea evans and minh collins 
hollywood and beyond podcast is available on:
apple podcasts, itunes, podbean, iheartradio, spotify, stitcher, google play music, radio public and tunein radio

created, produced, edited and hosted by:
steven brittingham 
contact steven: hollywoodandbeyondshow@gmail.com

music theme by: dario saraceno 
show greeting by: carrie mitchum

text_retweet:
look at this phenomenal quilt! 
#repost @huntersds with @get_repost
・・・
“why i’m a feminist”
🧡. it’s a personal story. it’s the story of so many of the things that have happened to me that showed me where my rights aren’t equal. where the world has been constructed for the privilege of men. where my body is not considered my own. where i’ve been penalized for being a woman, a mom. where the expectations of being nice anyway have cornered me and silenced me. where i knew something felt wrong but no one taught me it wasn’t okay. 🧡. i’m really proud of #metoo, but a lot of ugly things can hide beneath the hashtag. you know there is pain under there, but unless the story is told, you can avoid seeing it’s horrors. so i told my story. 🧡
as yet, every single woman i have shown this to has said yes, she could tell a similar story. every woman. and many of them have been matter-of-fact about it. think about that. this is systemic at an incredibly huge level. it happens to all of us, all the time. death by a thousand cuts. 🧡.
while this work is my story, i think the real story is that so many of us can tell a similar one. it breaks my heart, yet fires me up to fight, to vote, to speak up. 🧡.
i’m an artist. art is one of my languages, so i speak up here. we have used embroidery for centuries to learn our letters but also to teach our stories. so i used my needle to write mine. 🧡. made in 2018. digitally designed and hand embroidered by me. quilted by my dear friend @nstovall of @justquilting. and honored with 3rd place in the handwork category at quiltcon 2019. 
#quiltcon2019 #whyimafeminist #huntersdesignstudio

text:
​​#благодарность

здравствуйте дорогие редакторы и участники сайта nemolchi.uz.
спасибо вам за поддержку и ту силу которые передаете мне, и другим женщинам которые стали жертвами насилия. вы вчера прочли мою историю, в котором я написала что училась на юриста и что муж избивает меня: https://t.me/nemolchiuz/549 
я прочла все ваши комментарии и благодарна всем. хочу дополнить: я до рождения второго сына работала, сейчас нахожусь в декрете, т.к. маленькому еще 1.5 годика нет. в садик его не возьмут. насчет того, чтобы накатить на него заяву, я уж знаю наши законодательства, они не работают на практике, ну и муж работает в высокой должности в сфере внутренних дел, я не верю что кто то из органов  будет меня слушать.

но, прочтя ваши комментарии у меня изменился настрой, появилась  уверенность в себе. да, я найду другую работу, в котором рабочее время свободнее, найду няню для младшего и буду начинать жить заново. если муж еще раз попытается меня побить, я дам ответ, орать, кричать. но тем временем, я решила пойти в комитет женщин. если помогут реально найти жилье, я уйду с этого дома,  буду устроить новую и спокойную жизнь, без мужа и их родственников.  надеюсь мне помогут. спасибо всем.

text:
*trigger warning to the beautiful humans in my life* 
years ago a guy i thought was a friend did some pretty shitty things. as a result of his actions he was kicked out of the program we were apart of. he called me in tears several days before his flight asking me was what he did "really that bad?" he made me seriously question myself, after all, it could have been much worse. i ended the conversation telling him that he wasn't a bad guy and saying i'm sorry he had to leave. the night before he was sent home we hung out as a group.  he caught me at the table and tried to convince me that what he did was "not that bad" it was not "sexual harassment" and " i know what sexual harassment is..." i distinctly remember the whiteness of my knuckles as i stared at them holding the table to stop the shaking. i distictly remember my fear and my confusion. i distinctly remember blaming myself. years ago a guy i thought was a friend did some pretty shitty things. today a friend from the program started a group chat. the guy shared his good news about his happy life, i felt genuinely happy for him, everyone deserves happiness, but i did not respond. years ago a guy i thought was a friend did some pretty shitty things. today in our group chat he posted this. my heart raced. years ago a guy i thought was a friend did some shitty things. fuck. it was still raw. years ago a guy i thought was a friend did some shitty things. my stomach was in knots. years ago a guy i thought was a friend did some shitty things.  #metoo

text:
manifestera med #actionaid för kvinnors rätt till sin egen kropp på internationella kvinnodagen!

internationella kvinnodagen 2019 – drygt ett år efter #metoo. visste du att varje dag könsstympas över 5000 flickor? vissa av dem bor i sverige. våld mot kvinnor, sexuella trakasserier och övergrepp är fortfarande en del av vardagen. det sker i hemmet, på stan och på arbetsplatsen - i sverige och i övriga världen.

kom och lyssna på khadra seerar, zuhur adam och cecilia berger – kvinnor som kämpar för att förebygga könsstympning och för kvinnors rätt till sina egna kroppar. uppträder gör sångerskan sara celaya. under dagen kommer ni träffa fredrika ek som cyklat jorden runt till förmån för actionaid sweden arbete. på plats kommer ni även att kunna köpa våra senaste produkter designade av den feministiska influencern jessica hallbäck. var med och manifestera mot alla former av våld mot kvinnor!

vi ses på odenplan i stockholm den 8 mars från klockan 11.00. programmet börjar kl 16.00. varmt välkommen!

@fredrikaek @jessicahallback @celayaaa #internationellakvinnodagen #feminism #8mars #mänsvåldmotkvinnor #actionaidswe #thebikeramble #jessicahallbäck #amellmottagningen #khadraseerar #zuhuradam #saracelaya

text: “i was very lucky because i was never into drugs and alcohol, and i think that’s what saved me from danger. my friends and family were there for me, even when i was travelling by myself. that gave me the confidence to say no, because i always knew i had my home to come back to, and that they would be proud of me if i respected the values they taught me.” penelope cruz thinks that not being into drugs or alcohol probably saved her from getting into any #metoo-style danger in the film industry, but, she tells kate bussmann, she does think that some things in some of her movies might be done differently now. full interview in today’s sunday independent life magazine. #sindo

text: #metoo men det er den her jeg kalder det er ikke til noget twitter rektion tage med udja en meteorit det  så her er den jeg kørte gerne skrive mig så jeg synes det er en mand fuck det er tur på fødsel syg af det i går at du er en til kvinder er syv diesel som en sygdom vi som cyklister som har lige kørt der over #dogsofinstagram #catsofinstagram #picoftheday @nasaarmstrong sulten jeg vil gøren sige at vi måtte stoppe diske man får som gør rundt og gøre skaden er kvinder så det er planen at gøre verden rundt hvis du gør det der med at så vil du må gerne gemme 3,14 kr. så kan du lide din indkomst resten af din tid på jord det er tyk interesseret så slet bare den her jeg gør mit bedste til at respektere menneskets prix være der nede så de vil gøre privatliv her er en indtil ghani-hed som jeg skal have respekteret og jeg håber at dette til stykket arbejde, det gør det ikke rigtig som der de vil gerne giver mig 3,14 kr. det er ikea her er en indstøbt kære dig kære dig som pige (pi)solen, kvinder og frihed det er min sut k the i dag så vi cykler en styk kvinder så lov mig 3,14 kr. når jeg færdig med den så får den tilbage det er det er bare bobi jeg gøre og jeg mener ikke piger som flyver hen der blomster og tage den tilbage det var ikke det er der en af de hvide darwin snakke om det er det jeg gør søren det er en grund til at køre min egen ting der allerede er gjort jeg håber du kunne lide hvad jeg siger hvis de gør så vi gør det klokken 0 3,4 cola

text_retweet:
#repost @wsj ・・・
alexandra waterbury's world exploded after she filed a lawsuit in september against the new york city ballet and her ex-boyfriend, a former principal dancer with the company.

the 21-year-old's complaint described “the worst nightmare of every woman,” alleging that her ex-boyfriend had been secretly recording and photographing her while the two were engaged in sexual activities, and distributing those recordings and pictures without her knowledge to fellow nycb employees and even a donor.

for three years, waterbury danced up to 36 hours a week, graduating with an offer to turn pro. today, her professional dance career is over. "i think that’s what i would want [my legacy] to be," she said of being the only dancer to publicly come forward and to use her name in what has since become a major part of the ballet world's #metoo reckoning. "no matter how hard it is, or if it doesn’t necessarily benefit you…do the hard thing." read more at the link in our bio. 📷: @heathersten for @wsjmag
name: Alphalegacy

text:
meine geschichte : selbstverletzung 💗😕
-
vor ungefähr zwei jahren im winter  begann meine beste freundin sich selbst zu verletzen. im gegenteil zu anderen menschen wollte sie aufmerksamkeit legte ihre arme offen aus und ritzte sich im unterricht... sie sagte das helfe ihr wenn es ihr nicht gut geht... irgendwann begann ich das zu glauben und auszuprobieren. ich redete mir ein es würde helfen und alles würde besser werden.  am anfang verwendete ich abgebrochene kugelschreiber und mich selbst zu verletzen und selbst diese wunden gaben narben... als es dann richtung sommer ging wollte ich aufhören da es mir peinlich war meine narben zu zeigen doch auf einmal ging es nicht mehr,  ich war wie gefangen! im gegensatz zu meiner freundin konnte ich nicht aufhören. ich verletze mich immer schlimmer lief nur noch im pullover rum und bald stand das erste mal nähen an...
name: recovery von svv & Magersucht💗

vor ungefähr zwei jahren im winter  begann meine beste freundin sich selbst zu verletzen. im gegenteil zu anderen menschen wollte sie aufmerksamkeit legte ihre arme offen aus und ritzte sich im unterricht... sie sagte das helfe ihr wenn es ihr nicht gut geht... irgendwann begann ich das zu glauben und auszuprobieren. ich redete mir ein es würde helfen und alles würde besser werden.  am anfang verwendete ich abgebrochene kugelschreiber und mich selbst zu verletzen und selbst diese wunden gaben narben... als es dann richtung sommer ging wollte ich aufhören da es mir peinlich war meine narben zu zeigen doch auf einmal ging es nicht mehr,  ich war wie gefangen! im gegensatz zu meiner freundin konnte ich nicht aufhören. ich verletze mich immer schlimmer lief nur noch im pullover rum und bald stand das erste mal nähen an...

text:
8 mart'a takipcilerime ozel sadece hanimlara kanali oldugum ra sheeba enerjisi calismasi yapilacaktir. kayit icin dm .

ra sheeba calismasi oncesi dikkat edilmesi gereken hususlar:
.

1. ilik dus aliniz.
2. kahve asitli icecek alkol vb tuketmeyiniz.
3. calismaya katilacaginiz odayi arindiriniz. ( tutsu sirkeli su ile silme adacayi defne vs yakma dua okuma havalandirma vb).
4.o gunu sakin ve sevgi dolu gecirmeye niyet ediniz.
5. yardima ihtiyaci olan birine maddi/manevi bir yardimda bulununuz.
6.bol su tuketiniz.
7. calisma sirasinda los bir ortamda, mum, tutsu, tuz lambasi vs yakabilir, meditatif muzikler calabilirsiniz.
8. ortami elektromanyetik cihazlardan arindiriniz.
9. calisma 23.00 de baslayacak 30 dk surecektir.
10. calisma suresince uzanmanizda fayda vardir. olumlamalar yapabilir dua edebilirisiniz. kimsenin rahatsiz etmeyecegi bir odada olmaniz yararinizadir. calisma esnasinda uykuya dalabilirsiniz. endise etmeyin. hala sifalanmaya hatta daha yogun sifalanmaya gecmissinizdir.
11. bu calisma her calismads oldugu gibi farkindaligi artirmaya niyet eder. o nedenle calisma sonrasinda da farkinda olmaya anda kalmaya dikkat ediniz. haberci ruyalariniz olabilir. cevrenizdeki herseye ve herkese dikkat etmelisiniz ki ilahi mesajin nereden gelecegi bilinmez 😉😉😉
12. calisma sonrasinda tesekkur etmeyi sukretmeyi unutmayiniz..sukredelim ki sukrettiklerimizin sayisi artsin. ve unutmayalim ki istedigimiz ne varsa once ona layik oldugumuzu kabul edelim. cunku bilincaltinizda layik hissetmediginiz hic bir esya/mal/is/dua/bereket/ask/evlilik/cocuk akliniza ne gelirse bize gelmeyecektir.
.

#sağlıklıyaşam #nefesteknikleri #abundanceprosperity  #healing #motivasyon #pozitif #bilinç #düşünce #bollukbereketreikisi  #bollukbereketenerjisi #sevgi #enerji .
. 🍀ra-sheeba antik mısır uygarlığından kalma bir şifa öğretisidir, eril ve dişi enerjiyi dengeler ve güçlendirir. ’’ra’’ eril enerjiyi temsil eder. güneş tanrısı ve yaratıcı olarak bilinir. başında bir disk bulunan şahin kafalı insan görünümündedir.
.

text:
educar en la igualdad es esencial.
•
y no solo por una cuestión de equidad, sino también para asegurarnos de estar criando a personas independientes.
•
personas que el día de mañana sabrán valerse por sí solas, serán capaces de vivir con tranquilidad y sin nadie al lado porque podrán ocuparse de sí mismos.
•
es muy triste cuando se busca en la pareja a una madre sustituta, para que siga ocupándose de las tareas...
•
rompamos con esas ideas arcaicas y esos modelos educativos anticuados.
•
¡seamos la generación del cambio! que empiece ahora y siga evolucionando.

text: #metoo är en rörelse som startade 2017 och sedan växte sig stark under 2018. rörelsen är grundad på att kvinnor länge har fått stå ut med att bli trakasserade och diskriminerade av män, speciellt högt uppsatta män då de har mycket makt. nu vågar de tala högt om sina upplevelser, äntligen!! det har länge varit tabu och lagt stor skam över att berätta om vad man utsatts för. det är fantastiskt att folk nu vågar tala om orättvisor de ser och har upplevt och att så många människor runt om kring väljer att stödja dessa personerna. #moraliskthistoriebruk många feminister har dragit nytta av metoo rörelsen och använt händelser för att visa att samhället faktiskt är orättvist. med detta har de sedan lyft fram sin ideologi feminism, de vill att alla ska ha lika rättigheter. de vill att alla ska vara så politiskt, ekonomiskt och socialt lika som möjligt. detta är vägen mot rättvisa! #ideologiskthistoriebruk många menar att synen på kvinnor måste förändras i samband med att samhället förändras. det funkar inte att kvinnor och män ska ha olika roller i dagens samhälle. det var kanske så förr i tiden men inte längre. kvinnorna ska inte ta hand om familjen och männen ska inte arbeta utan det ska vara jämt fördelat. dessutom behövs det ingen som tar hand om familjen och hemmet på samma sätt som tidigare. det har uppfunnits så mycket prylar som gör vardagslivet lättare. män har inte mer rätt till ett arbete än kvinnor även fast det har varit så. därför kan inte män gå runt och tro att de har makt över kvinnor och behandla dem som de vill. ett exempel är luc besson som anklagades för sexuella trakasserier från 9 kvinnor, de flesta av dem skådespelare. som regissör har man en del makt över skådespelarna med det gäller att man nyttjar den rätt. det har luc besson inte gjort i dessa fallen. som man har man inte rätt att nyttja kvinnorna, bara för att de är kvinnor, även fast man sitter högre upp en dem i ett arbete. detta är bara ett exempel på hur vissa män tror att de fortfarande har makten.

.
there is a new/old way of being powerful in the world, running an empire and not losing touch with ourselves as women.
.

you’ve seen that woman who is just so happy, so satisfied with herself and everything in her world. she ooozes sensuality. it’s not flashy, it’s subtle. it’s in her small movements and the tone of her voice.

see how the world responds to this grounded, sensual energy!

text:
дискуссия «иркутская версия феминизима: как это?»
18:00, 25 февраля, понедельник, 18+ интеллектуальный досуг.
⠀
новая дискуссия кочующего дискуссионного пространства «хочешь поговорить об этом?» в «институте человека».
⠀
время: 25 февраля 2019 года 18:00.
место: «перцель», белый зал, ул. гаврилова, 1б.
вход свободный.
информация: (3952) 333-721, 610-317.
⠀
о дискуссии:
⠀
феминизм довольно давно стал одной из ключевых тем в публичном пространстве. всемирные акции вроде #metoo, политические высказывания и гражданский активизм, исследования и законодательные инициативы, издания, блоги, кафе для феминисток. иркутск в стороне от этой бурной жизни и напоминает тихую гавань.
ещё месяц назад, на волне очередной громкой истории, иркутский блогер и преподаватель игу сергей шмидт при встрече методично задавал каждому волнующий его вопрос: есть ли в иркутске феминизм и кто здесь считается и/или считает себя феминистками или феминистами? ответ чаще всего вызывал замешательство.
мы решили сделать эти поиски и разговор о феминизме в иркутске предметом дискуссии. мы попытаемся понять, так ли далёк иркутск от феминизма, как кажется. есть ли в городе запрос на феминизм и ответ на этот запрос. что подразумевают под феминизмом феминистки (а если удастся — и феминисты) разных поколений, взглядов и кругов общения, а заодно — сочувствующие и скептики.
модераторы: лариса салахова и сергей шмидт.
⠀
организаторы: центр независимых социальных исследований — иркутск при поддержке фонда президентских грантов
источник: https://www.irk.ru/afisha/sport/20190225/45157/

text:
esse vale a pena respostar... chegou a hora de repassar este ponto, em alto e bom som.

o tantra não é algo que você "aprende" dormindo com um professor ou curador.

a melhor maneira de incorporar o tantra é com suas próprias práticas e exercícios de oficina.

se você tentar "aprender" o tantra fazendo sexo com alguém em posição de autoridade sobre você, certamente haverá confusão.

a menos que você esteja completamente livre de traumas, sólido em seus limites, claro o que você quer, e totalmente fortalecido em sua sexualidade ... é melhor não se envolver sexualmente com uma figura de autoridade.

os riscos são que você será acionado em antigas memórias de tempos em que uma figura de autoridade se aproveitou de você.

você pode se sentir incapaz de expressar seus limites da mesma maneira que um amante de poder.

você pode se sentir confuso depois ... essencialmente, é importante saber que você não precisa ter o sexo para aprender tantra!

o tantra é, na verdade, a arte de usar sua energia sexual para impulsionar estados superiores de consciência.

você pode mover essa energia por conta própria, usando práticas tântricas específicas.

por favor, não desista do seu poder, esperando que alguém o salve, cure ou ilumine.

só você pode fazer isso!

by @shashi_solluna_tantra

#takebackyoursex #takebackyourpower #sextospirit #taotantricarts #sollunatantra #tantra #metoo #shaktijaya

os riscos são que você será acionado em antigas memórias de tempos em que uma figura de autoridade se aproveitou de você.

por favor, não desista do seu poder, esperando que alguém o salve, cure ou ilumine.

só você pode fazer isso!

text:
#ynaijanewestablishment: damilola marcus makes the ynaija new establishment list, 2019
.
damilola marcus (market march)
.

damilola marcus, or omogedami as she is more commonly referred to, is relatively new to the activism space. but her impact has been no less vital to the growing agitation for a re-evaluation of normalized behaviour in interpersonal relationships between men and women in nigeria. as part of a new wave of feminists who have taken their message online, marcus routinely engages in ranging conversations about the problems and needs of women in nigerian patriarchal society, garnering a strong following but also many detractors who see her defiance and passion for women’s rights as intimidating. ms. marcus doesn’t pay either her fans or detractors any mind, focused as she is on creating safe spaces for women to express themselves without the threat of violence or intimidation. .
.
in 2018, ms. marcus was one of the facilitators of the nigerian #metoo movement that saw teenage girls from a number of high-profile nigerian secondary schools detail abuse, rape and sexual harassment that happen with these institutions. having so many young women feel like they were given a space to express themselves encouraged marcus to take her activism offline and start ‘market march’, inspired by the routine complaints of sexual harassment by traders in lagos markets. in late 2018, market march organized its first offline protest march, choosing the notorious yaba and tejuosho market as its test grounds. though met with initial backlash, testimonials suggest that ms. marcus and market march made significant impact on the men of the market. .
.
while most people know damilola marcus as omogedami the feminist activist, ms. marcus is also an accomplished brand strategist and graphic designer, running a design label with her associate seyi olusanya. she also volunteers for organizations like stand to end rape and sanitary aid for nigerian girls.

text:
i was engaged at hearst castle and it was a place i had given up, it was too painful to consider going back for so many years. yesterday i went back with my brother 
trauma and pain don't heal themselves in my experience... time doesn't heal everything as we are told to believe. in order for me to return to this area and have gratitude for my pain is the biggest accomplishment of my life and only possible because of my sobriety, my commitment to my health and wellness. a tremendous amount of personal effort to transform and change myself allowed me to return with no sadness! 
letting go of the past and worrying about the future used to be how i spent my time until i realized that i have no control over anything but my reaction to life. it's so much better than to be stuck in denial, stuck in the past, wishing things could have been different.  now i know that the past can't be changed, no matter how much i want it to and to focus on the present moment. 
one of my favorite poems captures my feelings perfectly.... "tomorrow the sun will rise, either in splendour or behind a mask of clouds – but it will rise. until it does we have no stake in tomorrow for it is as yet unborn.

this leaves only one day – today – any man or woman can only fight the battles of one day. it’s only when you or i add the burdens of those awful eternities – yesterday and tomorrow – that we break down.

it is not the experience of today that drives people mad – it is the remorse or bitterness of yesterday or the dread of what tomorrow may bring.

so therefore let us live but one day at a time"

#freedom #california #californiaadventure #hearstcastle #letitgo #leavethepastbehind #drydiet #sober #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #transformation #empoweringwomen

text:
the first step to intuitive eating is realizing that the diet industry is a big business profiting off of you. we know that diets don’t work, which is why the industry has started selling you “lifestyle changes,” “wellness plans” and “clean eating.” it’s all the same. it’s all rules and restriction.
.
intuitive eating involves rejecting the little voice in your head that tells you you can’t have something you want. counting calories, setting rules and restricting to alter your appearance are all part of that diet mentality. . 
start to challenge that voice and you’re one step closer to eating intuitively. food freedom is possible. intuitive eating is possible. you are allowed to eat what you want, when you want. trust in yourself and your body. 💜

text:
nouvelle video (lien bio) spoiler : famille-amis-intimes (n'allez pas voir cette vidéo svp) 
#témoignage – #storytime 
#consentement sexuel, #viol, #agression sexuelle : ces fois où l’homme que je suis n’a pas su dire non !

témoignage très particulier, pour une fois sur mon site, ou même mes réseaux sociaux, mais témoignage nécessaire ! il y a quelques temps on a beaucoup mis en avant la vague #metoo.
sur mes réseaux, et dans ma création de contenus sur la #sexualité #masculine, je parle de bien être, d’épanouissement et de respect aussi.

le viol des hommes existe tout autant que celui des femmes, simplement la culture de la #masculinité, de la #virilité font qu’il est souvent dur d’en parler !
dans le milieu #gay, ou #libertin c ‘est tout aussi complexe, puisque c ‘est un lieu de rencontres sexuelles … donc on doit être normalement , ou du moins aux yeux de tous , open à la pluralité etc … alors que ce n’est pas forcement le cas …
dans cette vidéo , j’expose, et je ne cherche pas a être blâmé, ce que j’ai vécu il y a environ 15ans ! et qui, revient par flash depuis quelques mois, perturbant mon sommeil et ma vie quotidienne …

so imma say it.
i'm so sick of this divine feminine kick. sick of only female me too stories. sick of only women talking about abuse and rape from men.

when will there be pages about the healthy divine masculine and it's importance and power? when will we talk about the path and pleasure of a male tantric? when will we discuss men who have been raped and abused by both men and women? when will we let men embrace femininity instead of just women embracing their inner masculinity?

the world caters to men but only in the most superficial empty ways. when it comes to being emotionally well, healing, being spiritual, and having artistic expression, women are always the ones who get to do this feverishly. 
men take the time to heal and be yourself in the deepest of ways. feel deeply, be vulnerable, please! and women please help our men do this! it's their job to heal and grow but as friends, mothers, sisters, lovers, you should help your male friends find themselves and help them heal just like you help other girls.

text:
🎬 1. woman of substance by kaley isabella // 2. ballad of a female taxi driver from beirut  by naomi moser // 3. be bold for change by the progress film company // 4.  women empowerment mural by sober

as i was looking for empowering art vidéos to share, i realised that women empowerment is often only associated to gender based violence and i think it is problematic, of course those are very important issues that require awareness but it also give the perception and the narrative that only represent women as victims in need of saving from evil men.

women’s reluctance to identify with feminism has nothing to do with superficial reasons like branding. feminists should be asking themselves why so many women aren’t willing to join them under the feminist banner. one of the main reason why so many are just not interested in feminism is that it no longer seeks to make women free. instead, it treats women as vulnerable beings in need of protection from the outside world and implies that life for women in the 21rst century is unbearable and oppressive putting the emphasize on our short comings instead of on all our acheivements. western women, who are in a very privileged position compared to their sisters globally, are stereotyping themselves as damsels in distress incapable of functioning in the adult world, and in permanent need of rescuing. it’s as senseless as it is damaging a create a vicious circle. feminism is all about empowering women, but how can a woman be empowered when constantly undermined as a victim of rape culture, patriarchy , sexism and so on? 
there has been a cultural shift within feminism which has shifted the aim from female empowerment to status-by-victimhood. which threatens to undo the progress made for women, valorise fragility, discourage resilience, weaponise victimhood and fatally undermine gender relations. it’s not good for women to be treated as fragile victims rather than competent actors in the public sphere. it’s not good for either sex for men to become afraid that talking to women, complimenting women, criticising women, flirting with women or touching women in friendly greeting could destroy their lives.

women’s reluctance to identify with feminism has nothing to do with superficial reasons like branding. feminists should be asking themselves why so many women aren’t willing to join them under the feminist banner. one of the main reason why so many are just not interested in feminism is that it no longer seeks to make women free. instead, it treats women as vulnerable beings in need of protection from the outside world and implies that life for women in the 21rst century is unbearable and oppressive putting the emphasize on our sho comings instead of on all our acheivements. western women, who are in a very privileged position compared to their sisters globally, are stereotyping themselves as damsels in distress incapable of functioning in the adult world, and in permanent need of rescuing. it’s as senseless as it is damaging a create a vicious circle. feminism is all about empowering women, but how can a woman be empowered when constantly undermined as a victim of rape culture, patriarchy , sexism and so on? 
there has been a cultural shift within feminism which has shifted the aim from female empowerment to status-by-victimhood. which threatens to undo the progress made for women, valorise fragility, discourage resilience, weaponise victimhood and fatally undermine gender relations. it’s not good for women to be treated as fragile victims rather than competent actors in the public sphere. it’s not good for either sex for men to become afraid that talking to women, complimenting women, criticising women, fliing with women or touching women in friendly greeting could destroy their lives.

text: mais uma do nosso especial mulheres no cinema: ovacionado por 15 minutos na sua estreia em cannes, no ano passado, o filme libanês “cafarnaum” conta a história de uma criança de 12 anos que processa seus pais pela sua existência no mundo e todos os conflitos que ele precisa enfrentar dentro de um contexto sócio-político nada fácil. a diretora nadine labaki o define: “no fim do dia, essas crianças estão realmente pagando um preço muito alto por nossos conflitos, nossas guerras, nossos sistemas e nossas decisões estúpidas. senti a necessidade de falar sobre o problema, e estava pensando, se essas crianças pudessem conversar ou se expressar, o que diriam?”. esse é o quarto filme que ela dirige - sua carreira como atriz conta com 14 longas-metragens. “cafarnaum” é o único filme dirigido por uma mulher a concorrer na categoria de melhor filme estrangeiro. conheça mais sobre ela e sobre todas as outras mulheres indicadas a estatueta este ano clicando no link do perfil ❤️✨🎥 #aartedocinema #oscars2019 #womeninfilm #metoo #bestpicture #productiondesign

text:
i have always loved kesha. when i was a teenage alcoholic that couldn’t figure out how to love myself this woman gave me anthems to throw glitter to and disconnect from my pain.
during my college years, struggling with bulimia, i played the warrior album on repeat knowing this woman was fighting the same battle. 
having experienced sexual misconduct by someone close to me, my heart ached with this woman when she took her fight to capitol hill on behalf of all women. as far as i’m concerned, this woman sparked the #metoo movement. 
as a person that never quite fit the profile of heterosexually i cried watching kesha accept the @humanrightscampaign visibility award.
when the video for praying came out, my heart stood still hearing her discuss suicide with such bravery. i listened to her recite thoughts that had passed through my own mind more times than i could count when seeking sobriety and recovery. 
i let tears fall during the rainbow tour as she showed us the beautiful magic you can create from the darkness as long as you keep choosing to fight!
@iiswhoiis i can not thank you enough for the loving space you created for your animals on the cruise. i have never seen or felt so much fearless love in one place. i have never felt so at home or so brave and it all happened amongst a ship full of strangers. 
thank you for holding my hand, looking me in the eyes, and reminding me to take my recovery one day at a time. 
forever my magical rainbow idol 🌈 #keshacruise

when the video for praying came out, my hea stood still hearing her discuss suicide with such bravery. i listened to her recite thoughts that had passed through my own mind more times than i could count when seeking sobriety and recovery. 
i let tears fall during the rainbow tour as she showed us the beautiful magic you can create from the darkness as long as you keep choosing to fight!
 i can not thank you enough for the loving space you created for your animals on the cruise. i have never seen or felt so much fearless love in one place. i have never felt so at home or so brave and it all happened amongst a ship full of strangers. 
thank you for holding my hand, looking me in the eyes, and reminding me to take my recovery one day at a time. 
forever my magical rainbow idol 🌈

text:
//#itoowasmolested by my brother!//
.
.
“home is believed to be the safest place where you are always in the shelter of your family, father, mother, and brother. it is ironic how the place you are supposed to me safest turned into a nightmare for me. i was living in a nuclear family where my father was away making a living for a very long time while mom used to go out with her friends often in the night. i was left alone with my brother at home in those days when it all started. .
.
he used to invite me to his room to show adult movies leaving me uncomfortable. he asked me to act like what we just saw while instructing me to stay quiet about how he touches me or else he will get me thrown out of the house by our parents. i faced this all for some two years. the aftermaths were my dual attempts of suicide and breaking down in front of a psychologist. i am still unable to share it with my parents! i think this is the reality of every girl. all i can do is to hope for the world to be safer and better in the times to come.”
.
shall one tell her parents about molestation? share your views in comments! .
.
share your molestation stories with us! call out the elephant in the room. in this attempt, we will urge you to share this post and raise awareness. let us give enough confidence for our girls and guys to speak out against the molestation! .
.

text:
so few days back we were having a general discussion on dos and donts of an interview. one of the female colleagues shared her experience that  women have to be very careful about what we wear to our interviews because she had a bad experience once. this grabbed everyone's attention and we asked her what had happened. she did not even start to speak when one of the guy spoke his heart out... 'stop your metoo drama', he said and laughed casually. 
well, do you see anything funny here? no right? i thought the same... i did not know that we still have so many so-called educated men in our society who think that metoo moment is trash and its only a perception when we say that we live in a patriarchal society.

i asked him if he knew what was he talking about... to which he replied, 'oho! now you girls would attack me.' it is so disappointing that even today we have to share our experiences with everyone to tell them we face harassment every day since our childhood. yet, they don't believe us and label us as an attention seeker or would call it a publicity stunt.

our own uncle molested us when we were young in our own house, our school driver groped us while dropping us to the school, our father-like men stare at us in the market, our tutors harass us and what not.. these are not mere stories. i am sharing my friends' and my own experiences.

so dear men and women when next time someone is opening up and speaking to you about such experiences, please try to console them and listen to them instead of mocking them and shattering their confidence. we have a lot of molesters around us please do not  support them.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
kanwal ahmed founded the facebook group “soul sisters pakistan” with the focused purpose of cultivating a safe space for pakistani women to talk about their day to day concerns, and have the empathic, invested responses of the other women. they share posts as diverse as the excitement of buying new bangles, relatable memes, funny family mishaps to heartbreaking life tragedies. a lot of women shared their stories of harassment and rape on this forum at the peak of the #metoo movement, and as a result, several women opened up about it in the comments. in a culture where so many pakistani brothers were shocked at their sisters posting a #metoo status on facebook, soul sisters pakistan provided a safe and secure haven for several women brimming with their own stories of harassment and abuse. 
this is kanwal ahmad’s passion project and full time job- she doesn’t approve more than 200 posts daily, and ensures that the posts don’t get shared out of the group. she has a strict ethical policy too, and has successfully created a very comfortable space. she’s one of the two pakistanis (both women!) selected for facebook’s first community leadership program in 2018.

aurat march is about cultivating an empowered sisterhood between pakistani women, and kanwal ahmed’s brainchild “soul sisters pakistan” is one such desperately needed platform that cultivates strength through the exclusive connection that we women can offer to each other.

#everydayheroines #auratmarchlahore #humaurtain #soulsisterspakistan

text:
¡se fue una nueva #semanadebasta! 😍 ¿qué fue lo que más disfrutaste?

arrancamos con la visita de un rosarino que nos emocionó con su música en el #mateconzuker 🎸: ¡gracias, @gallardofabian! @rafadevilladominico la rompió en el #quéprefiererafa con hits como "árbol de cotorras" 🐦, ricardo canaletti contó todo sobre su libro "crímenes sorprendentes de la clase alta argentina" 🖋️, ilan llamó a su abuela betty en #llamáatusabuelos 👦🏻👵🏻, @juaferrari trajo la polémica sobre los tratamientos de conducto en @losdocumenjuanes 📽️, charlamos de todo con @gavinrossdale, vocalista de @bush 🎤, #marichongo nos ordenó en el amor 💗, escuchamos junto a @catarinaspinetta los hits del @lollapalozaar 💫, a días de su show en el campo de polo, nos visitó @djhernancattaneo 🎧, hablamos de todo con el dt de @brown_de_adroge, pablo vicó ⚽, @justlucam habló sobre #gandalf en #lucaatthemovies 🧙🏻‍♂️, @solesbarruti nos hizo pensar -una vez más- sobre la forma en la que comemos 🥕, @lolafonca explicó por qué #mirácomonosponemos no es lo mismo que #metoo 🎙️, ¡y cerramos la semana con un show acústico de lujo en el estudio cerati: el de @passengermusic! 🙌🏻🎶🎸 ¡reviví la #semanadebasta acá! ➡️ basta.metro951.com

so thankful for the opportunity to perform at @seawalkmusicfestival yesterday in #jacksonville! we shared the stage with some incredible artists, including @melodytrucksband! 
in all our excitement...taking advantage of the musician rv and making friends with the festival staff, shout out to sweet sue for putting up with the boys...we forgot to set up our camera stand so this visually obstructed footage is all we got, but much appreciate the good vibes from the unknown gentleman✌️✌️😂😂 only 5 mo’ days now til our new album, californ i ain’t, hits the world wide web! check out some of “who knows,” dedicated to all the females out there claiming their power! #metoo 
lyrics: 
this morning something’s different 
a hit of deja vu 
seeing things i shouldn’t 
must’ve come down with the flu

can’t touch it but i feel it
this wisdom’s old as earth
spirit moves inside me 
and it’s snaking up my curves 
but who knows what it means sometimes a dream is just a dream

oooh 
last thing, we play tonight at @texasrosesaloon so come on over #beaumont! we drove all the way from jacksonville to see you!! #fewmilessouth #fewmilessouthmusic @communityfirstseawalkmusicfest #seawalkmusicfestival #musicfestival #newmusic #albumrelease #californiaint #whoknows #texasrosesaloon #honkytonk #countrymusic #originalmusic #keepinitcountry

text:
according to the national sexual violence resource center * 1 in 5 women and 1 in 71 men will be raped at some point in their lives.
* in the united stares 1 in 3 women and 1 in 6 men experienced some form of contact sexual violence in their lifetime.
* 51.1% of female victims of rape reported being raped by an intimate partner and 40.8% by an acquaintance.
* 52.4% of male victims report being raped by an acquaintance and 15.1% by a stranger.
* 49.5% of multiracial women and over 45% of american indian/alaska native women were subjected to some form of contact sexual violence in their lifetime.
* 91% of victims of rape and sexual assault are female, and 9% are male * in 8 out of 10 cases of rape, the victim knew the perpetrator.
* 8% of rapes occur while the victim is at work. 
the problem of sexual violence runs rampant, and yet rape is the most under-reported crime; 63% of sexual assaults are not reported to police. of the remaining 37% that are reported less than 10% are instances of false reporting. the facts are clear, and still the culture that would rather victims of sexually based crimes remain silent prevails. 
join rebecca macceile as she throws off the shackles of silence and raises her voice. turquoise boot straps: a survivor’s thoughts provides a glimpse into her journey of self discovery while tackling many controversial topics at the height of the metoo era. #comingsoon #nonfiction #metoo #writingcommunity #authorsofinstagram #indiepublishing #linkinbio

text:
hi, my name is roxanne darling (@roxannedarling) and this was my week to takeover instagram from the los angeles center of photography (lacp) @la_centerofphoto. i am an emerging artist currently living in santa fe, nm. i love that lacp welcomes out-of-state photographers to be part of their community. 
this is my last post. i am grateful for the opportunity to share my work with you. you can find me @roxannedarling and my website is roxannedarling.com. keep in touch! thank you, lacp!

image: 
i am: sitting with my sweet and thorny memories

the photos i’m sharing this week are of me, from my series of portraits in nature. as a 66-year-old woman and emerging artist, i’m exploring the: * the natural desire to be unclothed outdoors, in the privacy of precious places; * a newly discovered quality of self-acceptance for my aging self; * an appetite to create art from the female gaze, as a type of reclaiming my time, my body, and my point of view.

the photos were taken in 2017-2018 on an extended rv trip around the western us with my partner. in many cases, the place itself spoke up first and invited me to explore ways of finding myself in nature. as a card-carrying member of the #metoo movement, i hope this work conveys a type of freedom of self-expression that is possible regardless of one’s painful past experiences.

the photos were shot using several cameras: iphone, dji drone, and a canon dslr. all images have been cropped square; some images have been slightly modified to meet instagram rules. *
*
*
#lacpinstagramtakeover #lacp #losangelescenterofphotography #lacpmember #lacenterofphoto #womenphotographers #picoftheday #iam #santafeartist #freethinker

text:
final hours for viewing jane anger by @rosemarymezadesplas at amos eno gallery. pictured here: “yo tambien” hand-seen gray human hair on black twill fabric, 25x21x2” .
come to #56bogart and catch the exhibition before it’s gone! closing at 6pm today, sunday, february 24.
jane anger features hand-sewn human hair drawings, watercolors and onsite installations. rosemary meza-desplas’ figurative artworks emphasize line and movement. the title refers to a 16th century pamphlet published in england titled jane anger, her protection for women.

meza-desplas explores the concept of anger as a tool for change by juxtaposing found imagery from social media, art history and mass media. she is interested in how the social movements, women’s marches and #metoo, harnessed anger in order to forefront an array of gender-based burdens. 
this exhibition includes meza-desplas’ most recent drawings which incorporate her gray hair. she has been sewing with her own hair since 2000. her hair is hand-sewn into a variety of grounds with small embroidery needles. meza-desplas’ decision to collect, sort and utilize hair as a vehicle for art-making is informed by socio-cultural symbolism, feminism and body issues, and religious symbolism. hair embodies a dichotomy: it can be sexy and engaging to people, on the other hand, it can be repulsive – like a hair in your soup or a hair on your hotel pillow. 
there are religious connotations to hair which coincide with symbolism reflecting strength, sensuality and reverence; such as delila cutting off samson’s hair and mary magdalen washing the feet of jesus with her hair.

.

.
if you don’t fit their mold☀️if they can’t figure you out☀️ if you are

truth: they may very well knock you down momentarily — but show them what “crazy” can do. ☀️not only will you bounce back up, but you will go get some more of your crazy and use it to fuel your gifts, your success and passion for helping others. ☀️
▪️crazy = exceptional
▪️crazy = excellent

.
.

text:
new post! #metoo healing part 2: media, truth & non-violence (satya & ahimsa) 💔 please read whole article @ www.sandihiggins.com thank you. ❤️ an excerpt: "sexual violence does not heal in private. it festers. the mediation of our #metoo stories – and the public investment therein – is essential to the healing of sexual violence because sexual violence is a social epidemic that can only survive if it can promote itself as something “private”. assuming that we want to end the epidemic of sexual violence that plagues the planet today – and that on this battlefield we are fighting for a healthier future for all – we must acknowledge that the media has a great responsibility to bring such “private” matters to the “public” in a skillful way that both public and private can win, or heal, together. skills are what we go to school to develop, along with knowledge. however, speaking from my personal and direct experience, the mediation of sexual violence has felt like an unskillful, losing battle... ✨
... according to rainn (@rainn), an american is sexually assaulted every 98 seconds. since reading this blog post, how many americans do you think have been sexually assaulted?

i am an american citizen and i was the victim of sexual violence in india.  i wonder: did this crime ever get counted? if so, where? as a statistic in india or in the usa?

where are such international crimes brought to justice?” 💐
🙏✨
#yogawithsandi

text:
it drives me mad sometimes that even though i’m almost 25 i’m still haunted by events that almost 15 years ago (between the ages of 7 and 11).
i’m sure i’ll never be 100% ‘better’ or ‘normal’ (whatever that means)...but i’m determined not to let events from my past dictate my present or future any longer. 
and with this determination i’m setting up this page, to document the struggles of surviving sexual abuse, and try to convince others (and myself) that it’s better out in the open than tied up in your head. ~bella x

pre_proc_tweet:
one year ago...
 hollywood's biggest night took time to deliver a timely message and celebrate diversity in filmmaking; 
ashley judd, salma hayek and annabella sciorra — three women who publicly accused harvey weinstein of sexual misconduct — took the stage together to introduce the segment.

when jimmy kimmel kicked off this year's oscars, he promised a light of positivity" during his opening monologue. during the third act of sunday's show, that promise materialized when the academy devoted a segment to honoring the  and time's up movements and highlighted the diversity in movie-making in the last year. "many spoke their truth and the journey ahead is long, but slowly a new path has emerged," said judd, referencing the women and men who have come forward to say  and time's up. those voices have joined together to create a "mighty chorus," she added. judd shared a hope that the next 90 years of the academy awards will "empower these limitless possibilities of equality, diversity inclusivity, intersectionality — that's what this year has promised us." hayek then introduced a pre-taped segment highlighting some of this year's most diverse and ground-breaking filmmakers — from greta gerwig and dee rees to  duvernay and kumail jiani — whom she referred to as "unstoppable spirits who kicked ass and broke through bias perceptions against their gender racer and ethnicity to tell their stories." jimmy kimmel said "we need to set an example and if we can work together here to stop sexual harassment in the workplace, women will only have to deal with harassment all the time, at every other place they go." perhaps speaking to critics of hollywood award shows who believe they have grown "too political," kimmel explained that the night's show would include brave and outspoken voices of the   and  movements in hopes of spurring positive change. "this is a night for positivity," he declared before rattling off all the names of nominees who had the potential to break or set new records if they were to win.

    scars2019

text: happy #international #womens #day. coming soon #8march #womensday #womenshistorymonth . i am pleased i was able to share the meaning and importance of this #day since the 1980s when i moved to #america . i worked with the government and introduced the concept of celebrating #iwd and the very first official bill in united states happened in 1994. since then, every year i speak at different organizations that support #women #humanrights #equalrights 🙏🏻🙏🏻🙏🏻 this year i will be supporting the puffragette movement, and windy borman’s film where one if the women featured is mellisa etheridge. #hero #inspiration. as we know medical marihuana helped many cancer patients and we’ll see and hear many testimonies. #grateful to all the #change that is happening in the #world and especially a big #shoutout to the #metoo #movement. 💋 i volunteer and also participate in #art #artauction where i #contribute my #artwork fundraising go to women’s health center or aids and cancer patients. celebrating could be listening to those that need to be heard. celebrating with those that are fighting for life and want to know that we have each other, we are one, we - people from all walks of life- just like stevie wonder said at one of the events that i produced... “that without each other we can’t exist” . happy women day !  what are you going to special on that day? #people #power #mindfulness #gratitude 🌺👁❤️👌 👏

text:
<3 <3 <3 
dankbar und unendlich glücklich, diese besondere frau in meinem leben zu haben - claudia von @traeumerherz_fotografie lebt ihre gaben nicht nur hinter der kamera, sondern springt auch gut gern mal davor als paola picasso ein und bemalt einen babybauch <3 mit einer lotusblume, die ihr so intuitiv gezwitschert wird und zufällig ;-) für das sinnbild der roten vagina steht <3

und so war es heut ganz leicht und irgendwie selbstverständlich, vor ihrer kamera zu stehen, ganz unbeschwert und magisch... unter anderem durfte sich göttin kali verkörpern, kali, die "heilige gebärende", die alles verschlingende und universelle all-schöpferin.
sie gilt als dreifache göttin mit den aspekten des todes bzw. der zerstörung, der bewahrung sowie der erneuerung und der schöpfung, beruhend auf dem glauben, dass leben und tod eine untrennbare einheit bilden und ohne zerstörung nichts neues entstehen kann.
kali beendet den zyklus der schwangerschaft und gebärt jenen der mutterschaft.

danke, liebe claudia, für den raum des urvertrauens, den du zu halten vermagst und der es ermöglicht, dass sich frauen so sehr in ihre mannigfaltige göttlichkeit gebären!! werbung wegen namensnennung

text:
two years ago today, i left georgia college. here’s a story about why. 
a few weeks before i left, i found my old phone that i used while dating my abuser, that had text messages from her on it where she admitted to sexually assaulting me. soon after, i went back to the title ix office to try and reopen the case i originally started that june. the title ix coordinator was weirdly nonchalant when she saw me. she was like “how is your semester going? how is everything? it’s so nice to see you!” as if we were old friends chatting about life. i told her i was doing very badly and had not been able to function since we last spoke. i was failing all of my classes. i saw my abuser almost daily and was having frequent panic attacks and nightmares. i was diagnosed with acute stress disorder and later ptsd. i had an eating disorder relapse directly due to not being able to deal with everything. 
the title ix coordinator looked at the text messages and later told me that there should be enough evidence to reopen the case, getting my hopes up, but a few weeks after, i was told there was still “insufficient evidence”. insufficient evidence, even though i had a lengthy confession typed out in clear english from madelyn. insufficient evidence. insufficient evidence. i had an entire diary on a password protected flash drive that listed all the trauma i went through during the relationship. i had pages and pages of notes on my computer detailing more things she did and titled it at the time with things like “public administration class notes” so when my abuser would go through my notes, she wouldn’t suspect anything and click on it. i had pictures of the bruises. witnesses of how isolated i became. i had her own poetry where she confessed how violent and manipulative she was. had evidence to show she lied in her original statement to the title ix coordinator. i had everything i needed to show that she abused me. all georgia college did was protect madelyn, telling me i was never allowed to say her name and what happened, unless i wanted to be charged with “retaliation”. i left because georgia college decided it was in their best interest to protect my abuser over me.

text:
i had the privilege of attending a jewish bat mitzvah celebration yesterday. during the silent period dedicated to personal reflection, i read this one from the prayer book. constant internal chatter overwhelms my everyday experience as an incest and illness survivor. the new neurological connections being formed, while old ones are being challenged. the general life questions that we all ask: what do i want, where am i going, who am i? all flood in and out and back around in me. so, it was a great reminder to let my internal voices find rest. i hope that for you, too. .
.
.
#rest #rejuvenation #love #peace #metoo #recovery #simplicity #wisdom #selfhelp #help #cure #spirituality #truth

text:
🏆hola oscar.
.
🎭la gala 91° de los premios óscar llegó y presentará muchas variantes este año. serán 3horas de premiaciones, estás preparando? te damos los datos más curiosos de la noche más importante del cine en hollywood.

luego de 30 años la ceremonia no tendrá un presentador oficial. diferentes artistas serán los encargados de presentar las 24 categorías de los premios y amenizar la velada.
.
🎼las 5 canciones nominadas solo contarán con 90 segundos para su interpretación, en este caso queen comenzará.

la orquesta filarmónica de los ángeles se presentará bajo la batuta del venezolano gustavo dudamel, está actuará en la ceremonia para recordar a los profesionales de la industria que fallecieron en los últimos meses.
.
🚺otro año para #metoo este movimiento hará presencia buscando la inclusión de la mujer. en esta oportunidad 51 mujeres se encuentran nominadas, aunque el 75% de los candidatos son hombres.

buscando la igualdad, de los 212 nominados 15 son afroamericanos, estos ocupan papeles principales como mejor director, actor secundario, entre otros.
.
🚫con la meta de que la premiación solo dure tres horas se dieron muchas variantes, algunas tuvieron que ser omitidas, cómo premiar a la película más popular.

durante los cortes comerciales se quería entregar cuatros estatuillas; montaje, maquillaje y peluquería, fotografía y corto de ficción, siendo esto anulado hace unas pocas semanas debido a las quejas.
.
📡el objetivo de la academia es duplicar el número de mujeres y minorías étnicas para el 2020 entre sus miembros. también desean llegar a un público más joven, aumentar la sintonía es importante ya que en los años anteriores no ha sido muy buena.
.
.
💥💡🔝📊💻📲

tweet_full:
🏆hola oscar.
.
🎭la gala 91° de los premios óscar llegó y presentará muchas variantes este año. serán 3horas de premiaciones, estás preparando? te damos los datos más curiosos de la noche más importante del cine en hollywood.

luego de 30 años la ceremonia no tendrá un presentador oficial. diferentes artistas serán los encargados de presentar las 24 categorías de los premios y amenizar la velada.
.
🎼las 5 canciones nominadas solo contarán con 90 segundos para su interpretación, en este caso queen comenzará.

la orquesta filarmónica de los ángeles se presentará bajo la batuta del venezolano gustavo dudamel, está actuará en la ceremonia para recordar a los profesionales de la industria que fallecieron en los últimos meses.
.
🚺otro año para #metoo este movimiento hará presencia buscando la inclusión de la mujer. en esta oportunidad 51 mujeres se encuentran nominadas, aunque el 75% de los candidatos son hombres.

buscando la igualdad, de los 212 nominados 15 son afroamericanos, estos ocupan papeles principales como mejor director, actor secundario, entre otros.
.
🚫con la meta de que la premiación solo dure tres horas se dieron muchas variantes, algunas tuvieron que ser omitidas, cómo premiar a la película más popular.

durante los cortes comerciales se quería entregar cuatros estatuillas; montaje, maquillaje y peluquería, fotografía y corto de ficción, siendo esto anulado hace unas pocas semanas debido a las quejas.
.
📡el objetivo de la academia es duplicar el número de mujeres y minorías étnicas para el 2020 entre sus miembros. también desean llegar a un público más joven, aumentar la sintonía es importante ya que en los años anteriores no ha sido muy buena.
.
.
💥💡🔝📊💻📲

text:
are you ready to celebrate international women’s day on the 8th of march? 
the theme for international women’s day 2019, is “think equal, build smart, innovate for change”. it  will focus on innovative ways in which we can advance gender equality and the empowerment of women, particularly in the areas of social protection systems, access to public services and sustainable infrastructure.

we kinda still need to celebrate women all around the world.  by promoting the social, cultural, political, and educational achievements of women and highlighting the struggles endured along their journeys to our children, it will inspire our future generations to be the catalysts for change that we still need in this world today. 
so yeah, let the planning begin!🎉 👊🙆‍♀️ 🤳

find out this year's theme, events and more: unwo.men/375r30ntsjy

photo by caitlyn wilson on unsplash

text:
are you living your life for yourself?  or are you living your life due to the expectations from someone else? are you happy?

when we make life choices for someone else, we are often left feeling unfulfilled, trapped, living the life of someone else.  it is exhausting.  it hurts.  it is not in alignment with who we are and our purpose.

do you want to make a change but i sure how?  let’s connect and discuss - click on link in bio @denisestyer to schedule a phone call with me to explore what this might look like 💜

text:
just had the best sunday morning conversation around our kitchen table wearing my "we are the village" shirt.

i want you all to know, no, need you all to know, that you are welcome here.

my vision is a world with more community and less walls. a world filled with "me too, brother" and "i hear you, sister". a world of see a need fill a need instead of waiting for a politician, celebrity or "someone more qualified" to step in.

the saying "it takes a village" is repeated often because it's true. raising children, being married, going to college, living life takes a village. it takes a community of people who are out for each other's good instead of out for themselves.

so, i want you to know you have permission to be your true self. you have the power to change someone's life for the better. you have the power to give to others who need. you have the power to be the light for those who are lost and just need someone to say "it's okay. you're welcome here."
.
friends, we are the village. together we can. and you are always, always welcome at my table, any time.

text:
“for most survivors, one primary thing, force feeds denial. [that is] they have detached themselves from their feelings. victims of violent crimes of rape and incest, regardless of their age, often shut down their emotions. this reaction is similar to the shock of physical trauma, in which victims often recall that they felt no pain at first. abuse victims understandably suffer an emotional shutdown as well as shutting down of the physical pain. the body and the mind both have protective overload devices to be used in crisis. these are, however, intended for temporary use only. the longer they remain in place, the more damage they do. when we as victims of abuse deny our abuse, we are actually lying to ourselves.” -shelter from the storm

text:
chances are you’ve seen the photograph of george mendonsa kissing greta zimmer friedman on v-j day in 1945. mendonsa died this week and within 24 hours of his passing, a sarasota, fla., statue that re-created his and friedman’s famous kiss was defaced with “#metoo.” today, the photo might be considered an assault.
•
the truth behind the photo: mendonsa, tipsy on a few drinks, had been on a date with his girlfriend at radio city music hall when he heard about the end of the war. they dashed into the street where he saw friedman, whose uniform reminded him of the nurses he’d served with overseas. kissing her, he later said, was a spontaneous act of gratitude. friedman, for her part, was caught off guard. “i did not see him approaching, and before i know it i was in this vise grip,” friedman once told an interviewer. (photo victor jorgensen / u.s. navy)

text:
i invite all readers to peruse seyed ahmad alhassan's explanation of this subject thouthfully and deeply, because he has responded to all the controversies surrounding the issue of the polygamy of the messenger of allah (pbuh).
in this regard,  he(pbuh) stated that: "but the issue of marriage at the time of the messenger of allah, mohammad (pbuh), and especially in the conditions of his life, even before islam, there were also numerous marriages, because of the increasing proportion of women to #men , and as it is clear that in order to solve this problem, there was  no acceptable social solution except polygamy. 
the reason why there was such a problem at that time was that there were constant wars and raids,
and this always let lots of men to be killed; while women stayed home and did not routinely go out and no danger threatened them, they were even captured and not killed like men in the wars. 
this increase in the number of women in those living conditions was such a social problem that many women who did not find a husband would raise flags for declaring their tendency to have sex with men, and #women who had red flags were famous in the society. 
many men killed their daughters in their infancy, a phenomenon that was known as burying-girls-alive, and the cause of this phenomenon was the increase in the number of women, most of whom did not achieve husbands, in the community and tended to have sexual relationships without a social law (like marriage). (facebook official page, 23/06/2013) * read the whole article in the site.

this increase in the number of women in those living conditions was such a social problem that many women who did not find a husband would raise flags for declaring their tendency to have sex with men, and  who had red flags were famous in the society. 
many men killed their daughters in their infancy, a phenomenon that was known as burying-girls-alive, and the cause of this phenomenon was the increase in the number of women, most of whom did not achieve husbands, in the community and tended to have sexual relationships without a social law (like marriage). text:
این عکس که روزی شاید نماد عشق بود حالا با یک چالش جدید روبرو شده است.  مجسمه ای از این بوسه ساعاتی بعد از مرگ جورج در آمریکا ساخته و در خیابانی نصب شد. اما طرفداران جنبش metoo روی پای مجسمه زن با رنگ قرمز همین عبارت را نوشتند. علت آن این است که گرتا فردمن(دختری که بوسیده میشود) پیش از مرگ درباره این عکس گفته بود که بوسیده شدنش با اختیار خودش نبوده و جورد ناگهان او را در آغوش گرفت و بوسید. طرفداران حقوق زنان معتقدند این عکس به نوعی اذیت و آزار یا تجاوز محسوب میشود و نباید نمادی از عشق در سال های جنگ تلقی شود.
.

text:
i invite all readers to peruse seyed ahmad alhassan's explanation of this subject thouthfully and deeply, because he has responded to all the controversies surrounding the issue of the polygamy of the messenger of allah (pbuh).
in this regard,  he(pbuh) stated that: "but the issue of marriage at the time of the messenger of allah, mohammad (pbuh), and especially in the conditions of his life, even before islam, there were also numerous marriages, because of the increasing proportion of women to #men , and as it is clear that in order to solve this problem, there was  no acceptable social solution except polygamy. 
the reason why there was such a problem at that time was that there were constant wars and raids,
and this always let lots of men to be killed; while women stayed home and did not routinely go out and no danger threatened them, they were even captured and not killed like men in the wars. 
this increase in the number of women in those living conditions was such a social problem that many women who did not find a husband would raise flags for declaring their tendency to have sex with men, and #women who had red flags were famous in the society. 
many men killed their daughters in their infancy, a phenomenon that was known as burying-girls-alive, and the cause of this phenomenon was the increase in the number of women, most of whom did not achieve husbands, in the community and tended to have sexual relationships without a social law (like marriage). (facebook official page, 23/06/2013) * read the whole article in the site.

text:
what i hold to be true most others don’t. or people are afraid to speak up / go against the grain. my girlfriend and i were talking about our own #metoo moments amongst other things and she said “we have to be the ones to say ‘no more’ “ and it’s true. some of us were chosen to lead the pack.

last year i went backwards a bit in regards to my own sexuality. after 12yrs of being sexually shamed by the one person who should have desired me the most, i had finally come into my own sexual and sensual power.

then an event took place and i thought. maybe i asked for it. maybe it was how i carried myself. maybe it’s because i was drinking. all the maybes went through my head.

but then i had to remember my own beliefs. no is no. boundaries are boundaries. as my therapist once told me, i should never ever have to dim my light to make others comfortable. i need, we all need to live fully how we feel comfortable.

i’ll tell you right now, most of the time when i’m home. i’ve got the least amount of clothing on, if any. & my blinds are usually open because i love natural light coming in. it’s my house, my body, and my right. that does not give anyone permission to violate my boundaries. no means no & stop means stop.

then @paigefilliater put all my thoughts and feelings around this into words: i could wear what i want and they can feel what they feel and they are given opportunities and tools to learn how to manage those feelings, how to leverage that power inside them and use that primal force for good. ours and theirs.

be playful, be sensual, be sexual. it’s your right simply because you were born!

name: Cel Ybarra
tweet_full:
what i hold to be true most others don’t. or people are afraid to speak up / go against the grain. my girlfriend and i were talking about our own #metoo moments amongst other things and she said “we have to be the ones to say ‘no more’ “ and it’s true. some of us were chosen to lead the pack.

last year i went backwards a bit in regards to my own sexuality. after 12yrs of being sexually shamed by the one person who should have desired me the most, i had finally come into my own sexual and sensual power.

then an event took place and i thought. maybe i asked for it. maybe it was how i carried myself. maybe it’s because i was drinking. all the maybes went through my head.

but then i had to remember my own beliefs. no is no. boundaries are boundaries. as my therapist once told me, i should never ever have to dim my light to make others comfortable. i need, we all need to live fully how we feel comfortable.

i’ll tell you right now, most of the time when i’m home. i’ve got the least amount of clothing on, if any. & my blinds are usually open because i love natural light coming in. it’s my house, my body, and my right. that does not give anyone permission to violate my boundaries. no means no & stop means stop.

then @paigefilliater put all my thoughts and feelings around this into words: i could wear what i want and they can feel what they feel and they are given opportunities and tools to learn how to manage those feelings, how to leverage that power inside them and use that primal force for good. ours and theirs.

be playful, be sensual, be sexual. it’s your right simply because you were born!

text:
i invite all readers to peruse seyed ahmad alhassan's explanation of this subject thouthfully and deeply, because he has responded to all the controversies surrounding the issue of the polygamy of the messenger of allah (pbuh).
in this regard,  he(pbuh) stated that: "but the issue of marriage at the time of the messenger of allah, mohammad (pbuh), and especially in the conditions of his life, even before islam, there were also numerous marriages, because of the increasing proportion of women to #men , and as it is clear that in order to solve this problem, there was  no acceptable social solution except polygamy. 
the reason why there was such a problem at that time was that there were constant wars and raids,
and this always let lots of men to be killed; while women stayed home and did not routinely go out and no danger threatened them, they were even captured and not killed like men in the wars. 
this increase in the number of women in those living conditions was such a social problem that many women who did not find a husband would raise flags for declaring their tendency to have sex with men, and #women who had red flags were famous in the society. 
many men killed their daughters in their infancy, a phenomenon that was known as burying-girls-alive, and the cause of this phenomenon was the increase in the number of women, most of whom did not achieve husbands, in the community and tended to have sexual relationships without a social law (like marriage). (facebook official page, 23/06/2013) * read the whole article in the site.

text:
alright. it's time i speak out. 
i got a message for the man i hung out with in november. the one i trusted as a friend for 3 years. a guy who helped me get through the 8th grade. 
just cause we were fond of each other. just because i hung out with you. that november. at the park does not mean that i wanted you to take that from me. i went home with you for a soda, not to have my very body and rights taken from me under you. 
do you hear me? 
do you see this message? 
are you still hurting girls? are you still thinking about me? and about how i told you no? are you still fantasizing about my pained face as i was about to cry from pain? can you still feel the fear of my shaking body? my breathe holding itself back? can you hear the choke in my throat from wanting to cry and break down?? can you still hear it? can you still see it?? ladies. be careful. most men will never understand. they can't comprehend the pain and emotional scars lefts behind from being raped. some can try, some will sympathize. 
others will ask for every gory detail. 
you tell them that you are not their porn. 
that your horror story is not their get off. 
some men will tell you to stop crying, cause they are stuck up. tell them to ask their mother or sister is they had been raped. ask them if they would want their beloved mothers or sisters degraded under another guy that way. 
if they still don't understand then they aren't going to understand. 
women who are silenced i won't tell a soul. 
cause i understand that after that you feel like your soul has left your body. 
this was my story. #metoo

in this regard,  he(pbuh) stated that: "but the issue of marriage at the time of the messenger of allah, mohammad (pbuh), and especially in the conditions of his life, even before islam, there were also numerous marriages, because of the increasing proportion of women to #men , and as it is clear that in order to solve this problem, there was  no acceptable social solution except polygamy. 
the reason why there was such a problem at that time was that there were constant wars and raids,
and this always let lots of men to be killed; while women stayed home and did not routinely go out and no danger threatened them, they were even captured and not killed like men in the wars. 
this increase in the number of women in those living conditions was such a social problem that many women who did not find a husband would raise flags for declaring their tendency to have sex with men, and #women who had red flags were famous in the society. 
many men killed their daughters in their infancy, a phenomenon that was known as burying-girls-alive, and the cause of this phenomenon was the increase in the number of women, most of whom did not achieve husbands, in the community and tended to have sexual relationships without a social law (like marriage). (facebook official page, 23/06/2013) * read the whole article in the site.

i invite all readers to peruse seyed ahmad alhassan's explanation of this subject thouthfully and deeply, because he has responded to all the controversies surrounding the issue of the polygamy of the messenger of allah (pbuh).
in this regard,  he(pbuh) stated that: "but the issue of marriage at the time of the messenger of allah, mohammad (pbuh), and especially in the conditions of his life, even before islam, there were also numerous marriages, because of the increasing proportion of women to #men , and as it is clear that in order to solve this problem, there was  no acceptable social solution except polygamy. 
the reason why there was such a problem at that time was that there were constant wars and raids,
and this always let lots of men to be killed; while women stayed home and did not routinely go out and no danger threatened them, they were even captured and not killed like men in the wars. 
this increase in the number of women in those living conditions was such a social problem that many women who did not find a husband would raise flags for declaring their tendency to have sex with men, and #women who had red flags were famous in the society. 
many men killed their daughters in their infancy, a phenomenon that was known as burying-girls-alive, and the cause of this phenomenon was the increase in the number of women, most of whom did not achieve husbands, in the community and tended to have sexual relationships without a social law (like marriage).
